for a glass of champagne?

23:43.160 --> 23:44.753
We won't be here that long.

23:49.680 --> 23:51.000
Kill him.

23:56.840 --> 23:58.114
(YELLING)

24:05.520 --> 24:07.875
Rip his fucking ass off.

24:09.080 --> 24:10.070
groans)

24:17.480 --> 24:19.551
That's my boy!

24:20.840 --> 24:21.830
(ELEVATOR DINGS OPEN)

24:24.640 --> 24:25.835
Thanks for the opportunity.

24:25.920 --> 24:28.309
You're most welcome.
Very impressive.

24:28.400 --> 24:30.914
That bit with the collar,
how did you do that?

24:31.000 --> 24:32.957
Like my saint of a mum
used to say,

24:33.040 --> 24:35.600
"Get them young and the
possibilities are endless."

24:35.680 --> 24:37.591
I thought it was
the Jesuits who said that.

24:37.680 --> 24:39.751
Aye. Probably got it
from my mum.

24:40.720 --> 24:43.155
If you want us back,
you do know where to find me.

24:43.240 --> 24:45.629
Oh, we certainly
want you back.

24:45.720 --> 24:50.396
Only, if you could make it a little
more entertaining next time.

24:50.720 --> 24:52.552
I'll see what I can do.

25:10.240 --> 25:12.834
Here, remember I told you
about that dream I had?

25:12.920 --> 25:14.718
What? The one with all
the birds in it? Yeah.

25:14.800 --> 25:16.837
Yeah.
Well, I figured it all out.

25:16.920 --> 25:19.196
Do you know who Freud is?
No.

25:19.280 --> 25:22.079
Well, that don't matter.
Freud was a genius.

25:22.280 --> 25:26.035
And his whole thing was that if you dream
something, it means something else.

25:26.120 --> 25:27.269
Yeah.

25:27.280 --> 25:30.079
Like the girls, the island, the drink.
Yeah, right.

25:30.160 --> 25:31.514
They were just symbols.

25:31.600 --> 25:34.638
What they actually represented
was, like, comfort, relaxation,

25:34.760 --> 25:35.830
(PIANO PLAYING)

25:35.920 --> 25:37.194
no worries.

25:37.280 --> 25:41.114
And then this swell turns up
offering us more money

25:41.200 --> 25:43.032
than we could save
in 20 years.

25:43.120 --> 25:45.191
Well, it all becomes clear,
doesn't it?

25:45.280 --> 25:48.159
The dream, the swell.
It means retirement.

25:48.240 --> 25:49.753
You get it?
Yeah.

25:50.960 --> 25:54.590
No more filthy collections.
No more beatings.

25:54.680 --> 25:59.151
Oh, I tell you,
I feel really good here.

25:59.640 --> 26:01.278
I feel generous.

26:01.520 --> 26:03.511
Danny, what do you want?

26:04.600 --> 26:06.955
A piano.
Excuse me?

26:08.080 --> 26:11.755
I want a piano.
A piano? Oh, yeah.

26:13.000 --> 26:14.991
How about a lobster dinner?

26:15.200 --> 26:16.634
I want a piano.

26:16.760 --> 26:19.320
How about a woman?
You've never had a woman.

26:19.400 --> 26:20.959
I want a piano.

26:21.480 --> 26:23.915
Danny, you're starting
to piss me off.

26:24.720 --> 26:26.279
I want a piano.

26:31.960 --> 26:34.190
That's what
I love about you, Danny.

26:35.080 --> 26:36.957
One thought at a time.

26:38.040 --> 26:41.954
That's what makes us such a good team.
The brains and the brawn.

26:42.040 --> 26:46.716
I'll tell you, this is
gonna be one lovely day.

26:49.000 --> 26:50.274
(TIRES SCREECHING)

27:02.800 --> 27:04.029
(SCREAMS)

27:07.120 --> 27:08.349
Let's go.

27:24.120 --> 27:25.394
(PANTING)

27:36.200 --> 27:38.032
Good morning, ladies.

27:38.760 --> 27:40.717
How are we all this morning?

27:42.400 --> 27:44.073
Here you are.

27:45.400 --> 27:47.994
You've been very patient
waiting for me, madam,

27:48.080 --> 27:51.675
so I'm going to
devote myself to you all day.

28:02.760 --> 28:04.194
Who's there?

28:05.240 --> 28:06.913
It's you, isn't it?

28:08.360 --> 28:09.395
Yes..

28:09.760 --> 28:11.273
Well, isn't that something?

28:13.120 --> 28:14.394
You know,

28:14.760 --> 28:18.719
(ECHOING) I went right home and I
told Victoria, my stepdaughter

28:18.840 --> 28:20.990
I told Victoria all about you.

28:38.040 --> 28:39.189
(GASPS)

28:56.320 --> 28:57.515
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

29:07.680 --> 29:08.829
Hello?

29:10.840 --> 29:12.751
Don't tell me
you're still asleep.

29:25.000 --> 29:26.274
Well, now.

29:27.760 --> 29:30.593
If I was a fellow who woke up
in a strange house

29:30.680 --> 29:35.516
wearing someone else's pajamas,
I would be pretty nervous.

29:35.600 --> 29:39.275
I'd try to find the safest
place I could to hide.

29:41.200 --> 29:42.713
Now, when I was a kid,

29:42.840 --> 29:46.470
the safest place
in the whole wide world was

29:47.160 --> 29:48.753
right where you are.

29:49.920 --> 29:51.877
It does feel safe,
doesn't it?

29:52.120 --> 29:56.318
Well, I figured a man who'd been out for
two days would wake up pretty hungry.

29:58.480 --> 30:00.915
So I hope you like
peanut butter and jelly.

30:01.600 --> 30:03.591
My name is Sam, remember?

30:04.920 --> 30:06.911
Okay, you take your time.

30:07.000 --> 30:10.038
Victoria and I are not big
on asking questions.

30:10.360 --> 30:12.397
Figure when
the person is ready,

30:13.200 --> 30:15.032
they'll give their answers.

30:15.160 --> 30:16.230
Okay?

30:22.200 --> 30:23.270
Okay.

30:24.640 --> 30:25.994
(JAZZ PLAYING ON PIANO)

31:10.600 --> 31:11.590
(KEYS JINGLE)

31:16.480 --> 31:17.595
(GASPS)

31:26.560 --> 31:27.630
Hi!

31:30.960 --> 31:32.075
He's cute.

31:32.200 --> 31:34.237
Really?
I like his haircut.

31:34.320 --> 31:36.596
It's like when I was six
and used to cut my own hair.

31:36.720 --> 31:38.836
Yeah, well...
You and Mom thought it was cute.

31:38.920 --> 31:41.514
He's not six.
More is than not, I bet.

31:42.000 --> 31:43.149
Does he like to read?

31:43.240 --> 31:44.355
Well, I don't know.

31:44.440 --> 31:47.080
Does he like to write?
Does he like to draw?

31:47.160 --> 31:50.391
Sweetie, I don't know
anything about him.

31:50.480 --> 31:52.517
Well, that's not
all together so.

31:52.840 --> 31:54.353
He likes music.

31:55.480 --> 31:56.470
Cool.

31:56.840 --> 31:57.830
(DOOR OPENS)

32:01.320 --> 32:02.355
Hi.

32:04.520 --> 32:06.511
Sam said you like music.

32:07.120 --> 32:08.997
You know how to use it?

32:09.360 --> 32:10.395
See?

32:13.360 --> 32:15.670
Nice, huh? Yeah.

32:15.880 --> 32:17.279
It was my dad's.

32:17.360 --> 32:19.954
He died before I was born
and then my mom gave it to me.

32:20.080 --> 32:23.277
But she died in a car accident.
But not until after she married Sam.

32:23.360 --> 32:25.112
He was my dad's best friend.

32:25.200 --> 32:27.953
Am I talking too much?
You know, 'cause I do that sometimes.

32:28.040 --> 32:32.193
And if you're bored listening and I just keep
going on and on, you just tell me, okay?

32:33.040 --> 32:35.156
I'm gonna go
help Sam with dinner.

32:35.240 --> 32:38.471
And you can join us if you'd
like or you can eat under here.

32:38.600 --> 32:42.070
You know, it's just the food goes
down easier if you eat it sitting up.

32:42.360 --> 32:44.112
You don't burp so much.

32:45.400 --> 32:47.118
My name's Victoria.

33:05.040 --> 33:06.553
Should I go get him?

33:07.160 --> 33:08.230
No.

33:08.760 --> 33:10.194
Let's let him get himself.

33:10.280 --> 33:12.032
Maybe he doesn't know how.

33:12.280 --> 33:15.193
Well, then, let's give him
the opportunity to learn.

33:16.120 --> 33:19.636
There's nothing like self-discovery
for turning a boy into a man.

33:19.720 --> 33:21.358
How do you know?
You never had a boy.

33:21.440 --> 33:24.080
I was speaking from self
experience, if you don't mind.

33:24.160 --> 33:25.309
I was a boy myself once,
you know.

33:25.440 --> 33:27.556
No way.
Yes, way.

33:28.720 --> 33:29.915
Come on.

33:30.920 --> 33:33.150
Thank you for the food
we're about to eat.

33:33.280 --> 33:35.635
Thank you for the peace
this house possesses.

33:35.720 --> 33:38.234
Thank you for another day
of health and happiness.

33:38.320 --> 33:39.993
And, please,

33:40.120 --> 33:43.317
make sure Victoria kicks butt
on her piano recital.

33:43.400 --> 33:45.630
I thought we're not supposed
to ask for things.

33:45.720 --> 33:47.279
Says who?
Says you.

33:47.360 --> 33:49.874
Since I was a little girl you
told me those are the rules.

33:49.960 --> 33:52.634
Oh, you mean I didn't tell you
about the special exemption

33:52.720 --> 33:54.199
for very important
piano recitals?

33:54.280 --> 33:58.035
Oh, yeah, right.
Exemptions. I buy that. Not.

33:58.120 --> 34:01.511
You know, I liked it better when you
just agreed with everything I said.

34:01.640 --> 34:03.392
How about some soup?

34:05.920 --> 34:07.274
VICTORIA: (WHISPERING)
There you go.

34:07.640 --> 34:09.790
Well, you're just in time.

34:10.960 --> 34:12.678
This is your place.

34:14.760 --> 34:16.159
Come on, sit down.

34:23.280 --> 34:24.509
Okay?

34:24.600 --> 34:26.830
Victoria, would you...
Oh, sure.

34:30.000 --> 34:31.513
Sam made this.

34:31.639 --> 34:35.190
It's his world-famous
potato and leek soup.

34:35.280 --> 34:36.793
World-famous.

34:40.159 --> 34:41.958
There's your napkin.

34:43.239 --> 34:44.389
Bread?

35:02.120 --> 35:03.315
Um, no.

35:03.800 --> 35:05.279
This is a spoon.

35:05.360 --> 35:07.237
And this is your spoon.

35:09.720 --> 35:11.074
Like this.

35:28.800 --> 35:30.029
(SLURPING)

35:32.400 --> 35:33.549
Oh, my God.

35:33.960 --> 35:35.030
(BURPS)

35:35.760 --> 35:36.830
(BURPS)

35:37.000 --> 35:39.310
Oh, great. A duet.

35:52.520 --> 35:54.477
My name is Danny.

36:03.280 --> 36:06.830
I think we won't put a bandage back on
and we'll let some air get to this.

36:06.920 --> 36:08.991
You're gonna be just fine.

36:09.760 --> 36:11.797
I've been meaning to ask you.

36:13.320 --> 36:14.799
What is this?

36:15.320 --> 36:17.152
Okay. No problem.

36:17.800 --> 36:19.791
I wasn't gonna take it off.

36:20.880 --> 36:23.076
You know, when I was kid,
I had a cowboy hat.

36:24.640 --> 36:28.076
I slept in it, I ate in it,
I bathed in it.

36:28.560 --> 36:31.757
Anybody tried to take it off,
that same reaction. So...

36:33.320 --> 36:34.754
Anyway, I've been thinking.

36:34.840 --> 36:37.958
You've been cooped up in here
for weeks now.

36:38.640 --> 36:42.076
Wouldn't you like
to get some fresh air?

36:42.600 --> 36:43.954
Stretch your legs?

36:44.040 --> 36:45.474
It's nice outside.

36:46.640 --> 36:48.278
It's nice in here.

36:49.640 --> 36:53.190
You're afraid that if you go out
you won't be able to come back in?

36:54.120 --> 36:55.758
We'll come back.

36:56.200 --> 36:57.474
Promise.

37:00.800 --> 37:02.393
To tell you the truth, I...

37:03.720 --> 37:05.119
I could use a little help.

37:05.240 --> 37:06.389
With pianos?

37:06.480 --> 37:07.914
Walking Victoria to school.

37:13.640 --> 37:15.472
VICTORIA: Here
you got sidewalk.

37:19.920 --> 37:20.990
Okay.

37:21.080 --> 37:23.071
All right, we'll be back
to get you at 3:00.

37:23.160 --> 37:24.230
I am 18, Sam.

37:24.320 --> 37:26.357
Yeah, for a whole week-and-a-half.
3:00. All right.

37:26.440 --> 37:27.714
Bye
Bye. '

37:27.960 --> 37:28.995
Bye.

37:33.240 --> 37:34.310
You all right?

37:34.680 --> 37:35.795
She kissed me.

37:35.880 --> 37:38.633
Yeah, I know,
she does that. How was it?

37:40.240 --> 37:42.117
Wet.
But is that all?

37:43.520 --> 37:44.635
Nice.

37:44.720 --> 37:46.040
Wet. Nice.

37:47.000 --> 37:50.630
Sounds like what a kiss ought to feel like.
Come on, we got a lot to do.

37:57.480 --> 37:59.790
Hello, love.
Oh, good morning, Maddy.

38:00.640 --> 38:03.393
Maddy runs the best supermarket
in all of Glasgow.

38:03.520 --> 38:06.273
Maddy, this is Danny.
Hello, Danny.

38:07.200 --> 38:10.158
He's a little shy.
Oh, I like my men to be shy.

38:10.240 --> 38:12.311
Presents a challenge
for a girl.

38:13.560 --> 38:15.870
I'm just gonna give him some of
the finer points of shopping.

38:15.960 --> 38:17.359
Couldn't have
a better teacher.

38:17.480 --> 38:18.959
Isn't that so?

38:19.160 --> 38:21.959
My mother could take
two stones and a cup of water

38:22.040 --> 38:24.190
and make a three-course meal.

38:24.840 --> 38:28.196
As soon as I was old enough, she
gave me the secret of great cooking.

38:28.280 --> 38:30.157
And now I'm gonna
teach it to you.

38:30.240 --> 38:32.516
So, you ready to learn
the secret to great cooking?

38:32.600 --> 38:34.796
Yes.
Okay, here it is.

38:34.920 --> 38:37.673
Food talks.
Food talks?

38:38.440 --> 38:39.714
You didn't know that,
did you?

38:40.080 --> 38:41.115
No.

38:41.200 --> 38:42.520
Food talks.

38:42.600 --> 38:45.319
It will tell you
everything you need to know.

38:45.400 --> 38:47.994
All you have to do
is learn the language.

38:48.360 --> 38:50.476
Take this melon here
for instance now.

38:50.560 --> 38:51.709
(TAPPING)

38:52.400 --> 38:54.471
What do you think
that's saying?

38:55.400 --> 38:56.595
(PUFFS)

38:56.760 --> 38:57.989
laughs)

38:58.920 --> 39:02.231
Yeah. But it's also saying,
"I am ripe."

39:03.080 --> 39:05.356
You know what ripe
means, don't you? No.

39:05.440 --> 39:08.956
Ripe means sweet
and sweet means good.

39:10.680 --> 39:12.557
The kiss was ripe.

39:14.280 --> 39:15.509
Uh,no,no.

39:15.600 --> 39:18.399
The kiss was sweet.
The melon is ripe.

39:19.280 --> 39:21.556
But ripe means sweet.

39:22.720 --> 39:25.519
Well, when you're
talking about food.

39:25.600 --> 39:28.592
Kisses are nourishing in their
own way, but kisses are...

39:29.880 --> 39:31.200
Kisses are complicated.

39:31.280 --> 39:32.953
For now,
let's just stick to melons.

39:33.280 --> 39:35.237
(INHALING DEEPLY)

39:36.000 --> 39:39.789
Good bread is fresh.
Here, smell it. Fresh.

39:41.120 --> 39:43.031
Fresh.
Fresh.

39:43.120 --> 39:45.873
Good. All right.
Get some bread, Danny.

39:53.160 --> 39:57.950
Okay, now comes
the hard part. Cooking.

39:59.640 --> 40:02.951
Over there in that cabinet,
there's a large, round pot.

40:03.040 --> 40:05.680
Would you get it for me? Okay.

40:09.280 --> 40:11.749
Now, when we
cook the food,

40:11.840 --> 40:13.990
it speaks to us
in another language,

40:14.080 --> 40:16.799
which we listen to with
our tongues, by tasting.

40:17.600 --> 40:18.920
Look at these beauties.

40:20.600 --> 40:21.829
Yeah.

40:23.640 --> 40:26.632
Now, you know you've got good sausage
when they're attached like this.

40:30.680 --> 40:31.795
Hmm.

40:33.000 --> 40:36.197
Found something, didn't you?
Now, let's see...

40:39.840 --> 40:42.719
That's Victoria when
she was a little baby.

40:44.320 --> 40:48.075
And that's Victoria
with her mom.

40:50.080 --> 40:51.878
Her father
was my best friend.

40:51.960 --> 40:54.236
He died before
Victoria was born.

40:58.600 --> 41:01.035
Her mother was
my best friend, also.

41:02.640 --> 41:03.630
So,

41:05.360 --> 41:08.557
after he died,
she and I got married.

41:10.640 --> 41:12.119
Then, there was
a car accident

41:12.200 --> 41:15.192
when Victoria was
seven years old.

41:15.280 --> 41:17.840
Her mother was killed,
and I lost my eyesight.

41:19.240 --> 41:21.470
Victoria was left with me.

41:22.800 --> 41:24.871
Funny how families
get made, isn't it?

41:28.080 --> 41:29.559
You got family?

41:29.640 --> 41:30.994
Don't know.

41:31.360 --> 41:34.273
Well, you must have.
Everybody's got family somewhere.

41:36.000 --> 41:37.559
I don't remember them.

41:39.680 --> 41:42.513
Well, maybe
you will one day.

41:45.560 --> 41:47.198
The pots are in there.

41:57.040 --> 41:58.917
Earth to Danny.

41:59.000 --> 42:01.469
Sam sent me.
All by yourself?

42:01.560 --> 42:04.279
Wow, big day!
We should celebrate.

42:04.360 --> 42:05.839
What's that?

42:05.960 --> 42:08.839
"Celebrate"? It means we
should do something special.

42:08.960 --> 42:10.678
Sam said right home.

42:11.960 --> 42:13.109
Come on.

42:16.440 --> 42:19.353
Here. Thank you. Come on.

42:19.440 --> 42:22.319
This is the cone
and this is the ice cream.

42:23.560 --> 42:25.790
You ever
have ice cream before?

42:25.880 --> 42:28.474
No. Well, this is
vanilla ice cream.

42:28.760 --> 42:30.273
Vanilla's white.

42:30.920 --> 42:33.480
Vanilla is white.
Go on, taste it.

42:43.640 --> 42:46.632
Oh, no.
Just work it around.

42:49.440 --> 42:50.430
(SWALLOWS)

42:50.520 --> 42:51.999
Oh, my God!

42:52.080 --> 42:56.153
You know the thing about ice cream is
first it's cold, but then it's sweet.

42:56.240 --> 43:00.871
And if you freeze your mouth out, you're
never gonna be able to taste the sweet part.

43:01.360 --> 43:03.237
So look,
here's how you do it. You...

43:03.320 --> 43:05.311
Sweet is good.
Yeah, right.

43:05.680 --> 43:07.193
So look, you lick

43:08.960 --> 43:10.280
like that.

43:13.000 --> 43:14.479
There you go.

43:17.080 --> 43:18.309
How's that?

43:24.520 --> 43:26.352
Look.
You're getting it everywhere.

43:28.200 --> 43:30.589
Shit. Actually,
we should really hurry.

43:30.680 --> 43:32.000
Come on.

43:33.240 --> 43:34.514
You okay?

43:35.960 --> 43:37.359
Finish it quickly.

43:37.440 --> 43:40.990
And remember, if Sam asks where we
were, you let me do the talking.

43:41.080 --> 43:44.630
If he knows we had ice cream before dinner,
he'll be pissed we ruined our appetite.

43:44.720 --> 43:46.074
Understand?

43:46.160 --> 43:47.753
What's appetite?

43:47.840 --> 43:50.514
Appetite's what you have if you don't
have a belly full of ice cream.

43:50.600 --> 43:51.829
How's my mouth?

43:52.560 --> 43:54.756
Nice.
No, it's not.

43:55.040 --> 43:58.271
It's full of hardware,
but not for much longer.

43:58.760 --> 44:00.558
Do you miss your mom?

44:02.040 --> 44:03.394
Every day.

44:03.960 --> 44:05.553
You miss your mom?

44:06.240 --> 44:08.197
I don't remember my mom.

44:08.680 --> 44:11.798
Sometimes I think it'd be
easier not to remember.

44:16.320 --> 44:17.390
Hi.

44:17.600 --> 44:18.635
Hi.

44:18.720 --> 44:19.869
You're late.

44:19.960 --> 44:23.715
It was so nice out we decided
to walk the long way.

44:23.800 --> 44:25.393
Oh, you...

44:26.400 --> 44:28.994
Didn't I say bring her
straight home?

44:29.120 --> 44:31.589
Sam, it was me, not him.

44:31.680 --> 44:32.909
Oh, it was...

44:33.120 --> 44:35.077
If you wanted to take
the long way home, Victoria,

44:35.160 --> 44:36.559
you could have gone
to that school in Kansas.

44:36.640 --> 44:38.631
Then you could have taken
the long way home for 50 miles

44:38.720 --> 44:40.518
and I wouldn't care!
50 miles of corn.

44:40.600 --> 44:42.398
Corn is safe.
Corn is boring.

44:42.480 --> 44:44.073
And anyway,
this was the better school.

44:44.240 --> 44:47.790
Which is why we're here
and not with the corn, right?

44:47.880 --> 44:49.518
So do me a favor.

44:49.960 --> 44:51.189
Don't make me worry.

44:51.440 --> 44:52.430
Okay, Sam.

44:52.600 --> 44:53.795
Au right.

44:55.280 --> 44:56.270
